DMG REDUCTION VS Shadowknights X% <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ullyapakadeabn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llyap aka Deabn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/5/02 11:09:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re</span><hr size=1> This is NOT a balance thread. Please try to stay on topic. If wizards can take you in a faire fight, Aerimus, go ahead and post how they do it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/7/02 10:16:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re</span><hr size=1> Why do I want wizard pks to have a fair chance against me /laugh?<br>
<br>
Heres one idea if you want to kill a melee indoors. Nuke him once, laugh at him and zone out get him where YOU want him.  If you piss him off enough he will follow you.<br>
<br>
If the melee has no signifigant means to regen health like a velious bp you can use hit and run tactics to run down their hp from max range without giving him a good chance to follow.  If used successfully you must really engage them before they drop too low in hp or they will just back off and head out.<br>
<br>
Ok opinions here... A 60 wiz even without AA isn't really weak.<br>
<br>
60 spells make a difference.<br>
Epic skin makes a substantial difference.<br>
Uber channeling at 60 makes a huge difference.  <br>
<br>
At least from my experience fighting 60s it seems its no longer a matter of can I keep them from casting, I can't without bash.  Its a matter of can I take them out fast enough to live through it.<br>
<br>
Bind in bizaar junk buff yourself fully then buy aego.  Port to the location that you wish to pvp in.<br>
<br>
Keep all neccesary mage focus items on a corpse when you log off if you can.  For pvp vs a pure melee you mainly need dmg focus range and haste.<br>
<br>
Aquire your epic and keep it up.<br>
<br>
Get a coldain ring or use a shaman ds potion. Its expensive (around 40pp a potion) to get the good stuff but it gives you a 31 point ds at 60)<br>
<br>
Put 2 insta clicky buffs in your first 2 buff slots and refresh them if dispelled.<br>
<br>
Don't annul a pure melee unless you have good reason to think hes buffed.<br>
<br>
For gods sake don't try to root them, not even that ghetto cold root.  Its futile unless they are a retard.<br>
<br>
Put on hp/ac (more hp than ac 30% more hp directly translates into 30% more dmg you can do and live) gear over everything else.  Maintain at least 70-100mr though just in case.  Maintain additional situational resists if neccesary.<br>
<br>
You will need +manna stuff for uber melees and plate tanks but for the low hp melees don't sweat it you could probably kill them with lures with the manna you have naked.  Get HP up.<br>
<br>
Don't be a dipshit and interupt your own spells when you would easily have channeled.  When not being bashed 60 wizards channel to a godly extent.<br>
<br>
Don't sit their and get pummeled through the  full cast time.  Move around and kite but don't be a wuss.  Especially if you have aego and epic skin + hp gear.<br>
<br>
Find a strategy in the middle and don't be afraid to take some damage.<br>
<br>
It might help you learn how to move better in pvp vs a melee to play a low lvl melee char.  I know playing a caster a bit effected how I fought them.<br>
<br>
Even indoors you potentially have a pretty free range of motion and can use levitate, position and in zone gate to your advantage.<br>
<br>
Example: Nuke gate to a nearby hidden point run out and nuke them again from behind repeat.<br>
<br>
Example: Levitate across the bridge area near the zone to Great divide in thurg.<br>
<br>
Example: Open the doors leading out to great divide inside thurgadin nuke the melee run through the doors closing them as you run.  They take time to finish closing and open again.  Use this time to nuke the melee.<br>
<br>
Don't stick around if you get jumped inside.  Always take the initiative and jump them first. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=atmas>Atmas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/16/02 9:51:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re</span><hr size=1> Yeah I can basically just say use lure if you got it.  Hopefully your channeling is good enough so that you can cast under being hit.  Yonder or shadowstep in areas that it is appropriate.  Skin ofcourse if you have it is very usefull because it absorbs life tap damage and gives no health to the Sk.  Thats real important because they have to pause to lifetap and it gives you a chance to get a free cast off.<br>
